Premier League legend Alan Shearer has named Super Eagles star, Emmanuel Dennis as one of the Premier League attackers for last weekend fixtures. Shearer picked Dennis among other 25 players to make up a full squad with the Nigeria international leading the attack alongside Mohamed Salah and Burnley’s Wout Weghorst Dennis was voted King of the Match in Watford against Aston Villa after scoring the only goal to give Roy Hodgson his first win since taking over as the club’s boss.. Dennis struck scored his ninth of the season with 12 minutes left on the clock powering home a header past goalkeeper Martinez. In his 4-3-3 formation, Shearer picked Wolves’ goalkeeper José Sá with a back four made up of Southampton’s Livramento, Tottenham’s Eric Dier, Nathan Collins of Burnley and Matt Targett (Newcastle United). In the midfield he chose Joe Willock, Emile Smith Rowe, with Harry Kane playing in an advanced midfield role. Wout Weghorst leads the line and the Burnley striker is flanked by Mohamed Salah and Dennis. 